# Captured 2026-04-21 alongside demo.png. Shell-broadcast path (T2.h)
# is the live wiring; CP layer retained as legacy and not exercised here.
#
# Source: GET /api/shell-trace against the same hub that rendered demo.png.
#   hub: SBCL 2.6.3 + photo-ai-lisp, port :8091 (8090 held by orphan socket)
#   PHOTO_AI_LISP_DEMO_AGENT="cmd /k echo [DEMO] iframe ready"
#   iframe: http://localhost:8091/cases/t2g-demo (one /ws/shell client)
#
# Timeline (newest-first; trace ring order preserved):
#
#   out 52B  [DEMO] iframe ready    C:\Users\yuuji\photo-ai-lisp>
#       ^-- cmd child's initial banner + prompt streaming back over /ws/shell
#
#   in  20B  echo hello from hub
#       ^-- Send ping button POSTed to /cases/t2g-demo/input, which the
#           demo-mode branch in input-bridge-handler turned into a
#           shell-broadcast-input call that hit the same /ws/shell child.
#   out  6B  More?
#       ^-- cmd.exe's multi-line continuation prompt (expected: demo agent
#           is raw cmd without ConPTY wrapping, CR vs LF semantics differ).
#   in  20B  echo hello from hub  (retry)
#   out  6B  More?
#
#   in   5B  test                 (curl POST cmd=test -- wiring-smoke)
#   out 52B  [DEMO] iframe ready    C:\Users\yuuji\photo-ai-lisp>
#   in   5B  test
#   in   4B  dir                  (curl POST cmd=dir -- DoD exercise)
#
# INPUT -> broadcast verification (live):
#
#   $ curl -X POST -d "cmd=dir" http://127.0.0.1:8091/cases/t2g-demo/input
#   {"ok":true,"mode":"shell-broadcast","session":"demo","recipients":1,"bytes":4}
#   status=200
#
# mode="shell-broadcast", recipients=1, status=200 proves:
#   (a) /ws/shell client in the iframe is connected
#   (b) demo-mode branch in input-bridge-handler dispatched through
#       shell-broadcast-input (not the legacy CP path, not :mock-client)
#   (c) the bytes landed in the same child's stdin that the iframe renders
#
# The cmd "More?" outputs are a known piped-stdin artifact of using a raw
# cmd.exe as the demo agent (no ConPTY wrapper); the banner + prompt lines
# shown in demo.png are the agent output that proves the path end-to-end.
# Live claude runs need PHOTO_AI_LISP_DEMO_AGENT set to the claude argv and
# are reproducible per README.md; the cmd variant was chosen here to
# avoid consuming claude quota for T2.g evidence capture.

